{
  "texts": [
    "A code with parameters [[n, k, d]] requires 2n physical qubits in total and achieves the net encoding rate r = k/2n (we round r down to the nearest inverse integer).",
    "Circuit-level distance dcirc is the minimum number of faulty operations in the syndrome measurement circuit required to generate a logical error without triggering any syndromes.",
    "|+〉 X Z Round 1 |+〉 |+〉 |+〉 |+〉 |+〉 X Z L R N e x t c y c le 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 |0〉 |0〉 |0〉 |0〉 |0〉 |0〉Fig. 2 | Syndrome measurement circuit.",
    "Full cycle of syndrome measurements relying on seven layers of CNOTs.",
    "We provide a local view of the circuit that only includes one data qubit from each register q(L) and q(R)."
